#  Virtual Machine Home Lab (Project 03)

##  Overview
This project is part of my IT portfolio roadmap where I built a virtual home lab environment to simulate real-world system administration and networking tasks.

---

##  Objective
- Create a virtual lab for hands-on practice
- Install and configure multiple operating systems
- Build a foundation for Active Directory and networking projects

---

##  Technologies Used
- Vmware Workstation
- Windows Server 2022
- Ubuntu Server
- Networking (NAT & Host-Only Adapter)

---

##  What I Did
- Installed Vmware Workstation and Extension Pack
- Created multiple virtual machines
- Installed Windows Server and Ubuntu Server
- Configured network adapters (NAT + Host-Only)
- Tested connectivity between virtual machines
- Took snapshots for backup and recovery

---

##  Network Setup
- Configured NAT for internet access
- Configured Host-Only network for internal communication
- Verified connectivity using ping between VMs

